main event: Observers at Kelly Air Force Base reported an elliptical-shaped light moving in the sky on June 16, 1953, with no identifiable aircraft present.
interesting points: The object appeared to be the size of an ordinary airplane,The object was observed for approximately 7 minutes and moved erratically,No physical evidence or identifiable cause was found,The observers reported that the sighting could be explained as a reflection of the sun on high clouds,Two airmen reported similar sightings without concern from the air police.
witness description: Airmen at the control tower at Kelly Air Base
